# {{service_title}}

{{service_description}}

A [Graph Horizon](https://thegraph.com) data service (**pipeline archetype**): the service
*is* the indexer. A `Substrate` streams events → pure `Handler`s transform them into a
`ChangeSet` → a `Sink` writes them to storage. A
[`horizon-core`](https://github.com/lodestar-team/horizon-core) gateway fronts the query
layer to take TAP payments.

> Generated by [lodestone](https://github.com/lodestar-team/lodestone). Experimental
> community project; not affiliated with The Graph Foundation or Edge & Node.

## Architecture

```
substrate (gRPC/firehose/RPC) --events--> Handler (pure decode) --ChangeSet--> Sink (Postgres)
                                                                                    |
consumer --TAP-Receipt--> {{service_slug}}-gateway (horizon-core) --proxy--> query layer (PostgREST)
                                |
                                +-- aggregator/collector -> {{service_name}}DataService.collect()
```

## Layout

```
contracts/                       {{service_name}}DataService.sol + interface, deploy, tests
crates/{{service_slug}}-core/      pipeline traits + types (Substrate/Handler/Sink, ChangeSet)
crates/{{service_slug}}-indexer/   the indexer runtime (mock substrate + stdout sink to start)
crates/{{service_slug}}-gateway/   the horizon-core payment gateway
gateway.example.toml             gateway config template
```

## Build + run the indexer

```bash
cargo build --release
cargo run -p {{service_slug}}-indexer    # prints synthetic ChangeSets via the mock substrate
```

Then make it real:
1. Replace `MockSubstrate` in `crates/{{service_slug}}-indexer/src/main.rs` with a real source
   (a Yellowstone/firehose gRPC client, an RPC poller, etc.).
2. Replace `ExampleHandler` with your decode logic — keep it pure and deterministic.
3. Replace `StdoutSink` with a Postgres sink (cursor persistence + a finalization sweeper
   that promotes `Confirmed` → `Finalized` on reorg resolution).

## Contracts + payments

Same as every Horizon service — see the proxy notes below.

```bash
./setup-contracts.sh && forge build && forge test
forge script contracts/script/Deploy.s.sol --rpc-url {{network}} \
  --private-key $PRIVATE_KEY --broadcast --verify -vvvv
```

Put the deployed proxy address into `gateway.toml` `[tap].data_service_address`, point
`backend.upstream_url` at your query layer (PostgREST is wired in `docker-compose.yml`),
then `docker compose up`. Run the indexer with the `indexer` profile once it's real:
`docker compose --profile indexer up`.

## Provider lifecycle (on-chain)

`provision → register → startService (per tier) → [collect]* → stopService → deregister`
